===Adjective===
{{en-adj|head=[[laissez]] [[faire]]}}

# {{context|economics|politics|lang=en}} Practicing or representing governmental [[noninterference]], or minimal interference, ''especially'' in economic affairs; pertaining to [[free market|free-market]] [[capitalism]].
#: ''I think the city should take a '''laissez faire''' approach to this; getting involved would only make things worse.''
# {{context|economics|politics|lang=en}} Advocating such noninterference.
#: ''The Senator claims to be '''laissez faire''', but he voted in favor of the subsidies.''
# {{context|economics|lang=en}} Resulting from such noninterference.
#: ''The price ceiling was well below the '''laissez faire''' price that demand would have supported, so there were always shortages.''
# {{context|of a person|lang=en}} Avoiding interference in other people's affairs; choosing to [[live and let live]].

